Element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem.quantity` is part of an existing definition because parent element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem` requires a cross-version extension. Element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem.quantity` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem.quantity`, but has no comparisons.

Element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem.item[x]` is part of an existing definition because parent element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem` requires a cross-version extension. Note that the target element context `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem.item[x]` is a choice-type element and cannot directly hold extensions. The context is moved up to parent element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem`. Element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem.item[x]` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem.item[x]`, but has no comparisons. The context is moved up to parent element `SupplyDelivery.suppliedItem`.

Note that the target element context `SupplyDelivery.occurrence[x]` is a choice-type element and cannot directly hold extensions. The context is moved up to parent element `SupplyDelivery`. Element `SupplyDelivery.occurrence[x]` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SupplyDelivery.occurrence[x]`, but has no comparisons. Note that the target element context `SupplyDelivery.occurrence[x]` is a choice-type element and cannot directly hold extensions. The context is moved up to parent element `SupplyDelivery`.
Element `SupplyDelivery.supplier` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SupplyDelivery.supplier`, but has no comparisons.
Element `SupplyDelivery.destination` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SupplyDelivery.destination`, but has no comparisons.

Note that there is an externally-defined extension that has been flagged as the representation of FHIR R5 element `SupplyDelivery.receiver` with an unmapped Reference type: `http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/alternate-reference`. Element `SupplyDelivery.receiver` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `SupplyDelivery.receiver`, but has no comparisons.
